# NET-NEW under lead-q3r1 (→ shopsystem-templates; new capability → assign_scenarios).
# Product authority 2026-06-29: "... there should be a doctor shell command that
# validates credentials and connections." This is the messaging-DB connection check
# of the new shop-templates-rendered "bin/doctor" command. It is the diagnosis
# counterpart to the SHOPMSG_DSN-unset bug (lead-j8so / scenario 214,
# @scenario_hash:a0342b1700fe27e7): doctor turns the gap an agent currently self-
# diagnoses into an explicit, named pass/fail line.
#
# WORK-SPLITTING: doctor performs several distinct checks; this is ONE check-behavior
# scenario (messaging-DB / SHOPMSG_DSN + postgres reachability). Sibling check
# scenarios: 216 (@scenario_hash:f55aa51f4bd138b3, agent-vault broker + CA trust)
# and 217 (@scenario_hash:5cf88671d3fab25b, CLAUDE_OAUTH). The top-level aggregate
# pass/fail behavior is scenario 218 (@scenario_hash:027a4d836bb1ae43). This split
# keeps each check single-behavior rather than one mega-scenario.
#
# Pins what doctor ASSERTS (the diagnosis surface: the check's name, its pass/fail
# status, and a remediation hint on failure), NOT how the reachability probe is
# implemented.
#
# @bc: and the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's; the
# block-only @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.
@scenario_hash:a6f8c0656a9e1cd9
Scenario: the rendered "bin/doctor" connectivity check for messaging asserts SHOPMSG_DSN is set and the product postgres is reachable, reporting a named pass/fail line with a remediation hint on failure
  Given a "lead" shop bootstrapped by "shop-templates" with the rendered ops command "bin/doctor"
  When the operator runs "bin/doctor" in a session whose "SHOPMSG_DSN" is set and whose product postgres is reachable at that DSN
  Then "bin/doctor" emits a check line named for the messaging-DB connection (a "SHOPMSG_DSN / postgres" check) whose status is an explicit pass
  And the same check, run in a session where "SHOPMSG_DSN" is unset or points at a postgres that is not reachable, emits that same named check line whose status is an explicit fail
  And the fail line carries a remediation hint naming the corrective action (set "SHOPMSG_DSN" / bring up the product postgres) rather than only reporting that the check failed
